## Response Format

Respond with a JSON object in exactly this format:
```json
{
  "tracks": [
    {
      "id": "track_id_from_library",
      "name": "Track Name",
      "artist": "Artist Name",
      "reason": "Brief explanation of why this track fits"
    }
  ],
  "flow_description": "A short paragraph describing the overall flow and vibe of this mixtape",
  "opening_thoughts": "What the DJ would say to introduce this mixtape (1-2 sentences, in character)",
  "closing_thoughts": "What the DJ would say to close out this mixtape (1-2 sentences, in character)"
}
```

Important guidelines:
- Use ONLY track IDs from the "Available Library" section above
- Include exactly {{ .MaxTracks }} tracks (or fewer if the library doesn't have enough suitable tracks)
- Order tracks intentionally to create a listening journey
- The "reason" should be brief (under 20 words)
- Stay in character as {{ .DJName }} for the opening and closing thoughts
- Do NOT include trailing commas in JSON arrays or objects (e.g., use {"key": "value"} not {"key": "value",})

Ensure your response is valid JSON. Do not include any text before or after the JSON object.
